SELECT 1;
$$ LANGUAGE sql;
SELECT * FROM produce_a_table() AS s (c1 INT);
SELECT * FROM produce_a_table() AS s (c1);
SELECT * FROM DBLINK('dbname=mydb', 'SELECT proname, prosrc FROM pg_proc') AS t1;' The 'AS s (c1 INT)' has a typed alias, while 'AS s (c1)' and 'AS t1' do not. In this case, the second call of 'produce_a_table()' and 'DBLINK()' will be highlighted.

